List of the main macros to run simulations described in chapter 8,
Domains
################################################################################

Macros k.*.mac are the corresponding KUPLOT macros to create a plot of
the structure and/or intensity distribution

################################################################################


dom.cube.mac             Simple cube shaped domain
                         k.simple

dom.tilt.mac             Cube shaped domain, filled with tilted structure
                         k.simple

dom.discus.mac           Creates fuzzy domain that spells out DISCUS
                         k.simple

dom.shear.mac            Sheared domain
                         k.simple

dom.lattice.mac          Grid of planar domains
                         k.simple

dom.domain.mac           Simple cube shaped domain, alternative algorithm
                         k.simple

dom.triangle.mac         Triangular shaped domains of different sizes
                         k.triangle

dom.spheres.mac          Short range order between two domain types
                         k.spheres

dom.perov.mac            Perovskite type domains
                         k.perov

dom.urea.make.chain.mac  Makes a single Alkane chain and calculates the Fourier
                         k.alkane

dom.urea.mac             Distribution of alkane molecules in urea channels
                         k.urea

dom.urea.stack.mac       Distribution of alkane chains along a single channel
                         k.urea.stack

